statement_latex:
Let A be a $2\times{2}$ matrix which transforms

\begin{align*}
\begin{bmatrix}
1\\
1
\end{bmatrix} \quad \text{to} \quad \begin{bmatrix}
2\\
2
\end{bmatrix}
\end{align*}

and transforms

\begin{align*}
\begin{bmatrix}
1\\
-1
\end{bmatrix} \quad \text{to} \quad \begin{bmatrix}
0\\
0
\end{bmatrix}.
\end{align*}

Is A invertible? Justify briefly.
